[size=150]Modifications[/size]


Third-party AHK files can be placed in the â€œ[c]DSLKeyPad\Mods\[/c]â€ directory as â€œmodsâ€ for the program. With modifications, you can significantly customize the program, for example, adding even a hundred new â€œAlternative Inputâ€ modes or introducing an entirely new, independent feature.


[spoiler2="Details"]

To create a mod, you need to create a folder with the following basic structure:

[code]
Mods/
â””â”€â”€ <MOD NAME>/
    â”œâ”€â”€ index.ahk
    â”œâ”€â”€ options.ini
    â””â”€â”€ preview.(ico|jpg|png) (optional file)
[/code]

The [c]index.ahk[/c] file will contain the modâ€™s logic and you can connect other AHK files to it via [c]#Include[/c] (no different from an independent AHK script).

The [c]options.ini[/c] file (UTFâˆ’16 LE):

[code=ini]
[options]
title=<TITLE>
version=<VERSION>
type=<LOAD TYPE>
author=<AUTHOR> ; (optionally add @<LINK>)
url=<MOD PAGE LINK>
description=<DESCRIPTION>
; Localized variants
[ru-RU] ; (or other language code)
title=â€¦
author=â€¦
description=â€¦
[/code]

The load type can be [c]pre_init[/c] (for loading before main initialization) or [c]post_init[/c] (for loading after it).

Mods are automatically picked up. After adding a new mod, you should wait 5 seconds before restarting the program.

You can toggle mods through the GUI: Tray Menu â†’ Modifications.

PS. If you need to get the path to your mod's folder â€” it is automatically saved in [c]mods["<MOD NAME>"][/c].

PSS. Mods are not isolated scripts from each other, i.e. conflicts in variable and class names are possible.

More detailed modding guide will be created in the future with development of the documentation website. You can find more complex mod example [url=https://github.com/DemerNkardaz/DSL-KeyPad-Custom-Files/tree/master/Mods/Old%20Mongolian%20Sample%20Mod]here[/url], but [c]index.ahk[/c] have comments on Russian and other files has no comments.

